import React from 'react';
import {
  View,
  Text,
  Button,
  Box,
  Stack,
  Image,
  AspectRatio,

  VStack,
  Center,
} from 'native-base';

const Hero = ({ handleLogout }) => {
  return (
    <View>
      <VStack space={4} alignItems="center">
        <Center>
          <Box>
            <Button position="relative" left={0} top={0} variant="outline" onPress={handleLogout}>
              Logout
            </Button>
              <Image
                source={require('./assets/keeper.png')}
                width="150px"
                height="150px"
                alt="logo"
              />
          </Box>
        </Center>
        <Center>
          <Text color="white" fontSize="lg">
            Welcome to Keeper ðŸ“¦ the storage Application
          </Text>
          <HStack>
            <Box></Box>
            <Box></Box>
          </HStack>
        </Center>
      </VStack>
      {/* <keeper/> */}
    </View>
  );
};

export default Hero;
